Wingman nick comes from the name of my son's old joystick that he bought at Wal Mart. How about that? But, my purpose in using it is that I am your wingman in that I am here for you and all the other Vietnam Vets. We should be here for each other - be each other's wingmen. Lighten the load, if we can, just like when the shit was flying. That's the key to the whole thing. We were there - we have the same point of reference!<br><br>
By the way, I was 11C 81mm Mortars, infantry, and served with some very brave men! <br><br>
Not aircraft. But still your wingman.<br><br>

